    </p>
    <p>
        All owners who ended the season negative need to have their money paid to the Treasurer by Super Bowl.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h3>Tie Breakers:</h3>

    <p>
        Ties are won by the highest seeded owner.  During the regular season the highest seeded is the owner who drafted last in the first round of the first draft.  The owner who had the first pick is the lowest seed and loses all ties.   During the Play-offs the owner who finished first during the regular season is the highest seed in the play-offs.  A Super Bowl that ends in a tie will remain a tie and there will be two League Champions.
    </p>
